net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class Tree

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Tree
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, EventListener, net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocaleContextSource, ColumnModelProvider, Component, TreeModelListener, TreeSelectionListener, TreeTraverseListener, Pageable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataColumnTree

    public class Tree
extends ComponentImpl
implements Pageable, TreeModelListener, TreeTraverseListener, TreeSelectionListener, ColumnModelProvider

    A Tree object displays data in a hierarchy structure commonly known as a tree. The data model used is a TreeModel.

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

      • preRenderProcess

        public void preRenderProcess(net.proteusframework.internet.http.Request request,
                    net.proteusframework.internet.http.Response response,
                    RendererEditorState<?> state)
        Calls ComponentImpl.preRenderProcess(Request, Response, RendererEditorState) . on all renderers/editors. Allow the component to process any form fields before rendering. This method must be called by subclasses. Method calls on components, creating or destroying components, or nearly everything else having to do with the component tree and related data models must be done by queuing an event using EventQueue.queue(EventQueueElement). Otherwise you may get unexpected results.
        Specified by:

        Overrides:
